<example id="1" format="line_items">
<input>
An e-commerce company needs a checkout optimization project with one-click payments, anti-fraud checks, and analytics dashboards.
</input>
<output>
1. Discovery and KPI alignment - Base: 10h - Buffer: 2h - Product Manager
2. Checkout UX redesign - Base: 26h - Buffer: 4h - Product Designer
3. Payment integration hardening - Base: 44h - Buffer: 8h - Backend Engineer
4. Fraud rule engine integration - Base: 28h - Buffer: 5h - Backend Engineer
5. Frontend checkout implementation - Base: 40h - Buffer: 6h - Frontend Engineer
6. Funnel analytics instrumentation - Base: 18h - Buffer: 3h - Data Engineer
7. QA and regression testing - Base: 22h - Buffer: 4h - QA Engineer
Total base hours: 188h
Total buffer hours: 32h
Total planned hours: 220h
</output>
</example>

<example id="2" format="narrative">
<input>
A healthtech startup needs an internal scheduling platform for clinics, including permissions, audit logs, and monthly performance reports.
</input>
<output>
Scope summary: Internal scheduling platform with secure role management and reporting.
Effort breakdown: Discovery (14h), architecture and data model (26h), backend services (52h), frontend modules (46h), reporting (24h), QA (24h), rollout support (12h).
Assumptions: Existing SSO provider is available and clinic workflows are frozen after week 1.
Top risks: Late changes in compliance requirements and unclear reporting metrics.
Suggested timeline: 7-9 weeks with a 15% contingency buffer.
</output>
</example>
